==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shafted
<hw>Shaft"ed</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Furnished with a
shaft, or with shafts; <as>as, a <ex>shafted</ex> arch</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>Having a shaft; -- applied to a
spear when the head and the shaft are of different tinctures.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shafting</ent>⟦br⟧
